      • setSoundEnabled

        public static void setSoundEnabled(boolean isSoundEnabled)
        This procedure sets the starting state of the sound in an advertisement.
        Parameters:
        isSoundEnabled - True indicates that the advert should run with the same mute/volume settings as the enclosing app. False indicates that the advert should always start muted. Note that a user can still mute/unmute the sound.

      • setBackButtonEnabled

        public static void setBackButtonEnabled(boolean isBackButtonEnabled)
        This procedure sets whether the back button is allowed during the video in interstitial adverts.
        Parameters:
        isBackButtonEnabled - True indicates that the back button is enabled, and pressing it will stop the current video. False (the default) will disable the back button during the video, so pressing it wil have no effect until the video is done. (Or until the user presses the 'x' to stop the video.)

      • setIncentivizedBackButtonEnabled

        public static void setIncentivizedBackButtonEnabled(boolean isBackButtonEnabled)
        This procedure sets whether the back button is allowed during the video in incentivized adverts.
        Parameters:
        isBackButtonEnabled - True (the default) indicates that the back button is enabled, and pressing it will stop the current video. False will disable the back button during the video, so pressing it wil have no effect until the video is done. (Or until the user presses the 'x' to stop the video.)

      • getSoundEnabled

        public static boolean getSoundEnabled()
        This procedure will return a boolean indicating whether an advertisement will start with its sound enabled.
        Returns:
        Returns True if advertisements should run with the same mute/volume settings as the enclosing app. False indicates that the advert should always start muted. Note that a user can still mute/unmute the sound.

      • isVideoAvailable

        public static boolean isVideoAvailable()
        Function to check to see if VunglePub has an advertisement to display. Several factors could result in there not being an advertisement ready:
        • If the library wasn't initialized.
        • If an advertisement hasn't been download yet.
        • If the device isn't connected to the internet, or isn't connected to the device's external storage.
        • If we've viewed another advertisement recently. (Within the delay value for your app on the Vungle Dashboard.)
        • If the server doesn't have an advertisement to show us.
        Returns:
        True if a video is available; False otherwise.

      • isVideoAvailable

        public static boolean isVideoAvailable(boolean debug)
        This function will yield the same results as isVideoAvailable(), but when the input boolean is 'true', the reason why an ad isn't available is provided to LogCat.
        Parameters:
        debug - Whether to print a reason to LogCat.
        Returns:
        True if a video is available; False otherwise.
